HEADWORD: Italianism
<hw>I*tal"ian*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
word, phrase, or idiom, peculiar to the Italians; an
Italicism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Attachment to, or sympathy for, Italy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Italianize</ent>⟦br⟧
